caption.text:
[CANNIBALISMO]

The illustration series is a study of the body horror genre, the manipulation of flesh and human anatomy. The illustration series is comprised of three parts embodied in three different characters that used to convey the three stages of cannibalism. Cannibalism is used as an irony to explore the fear of one's flesh, what horror truly lies inside of us. The theme is used to explore the multifaceted human condition at the core. These three characters explores the suppressed will inside humanity, the altruist nature, and the savagery that often times are uneasy to process yet we possess. Often times, one of these characters are the layers of which human chose to live. It's an elaborated exemplary of modern economy, filled with the horrors of the flesh.  #32artaward #makealegacy

Artworks inspired by the study of the body horror genre. Fear is what truly binds us as human being, the fear of what is inside of us that is truly visceral and macabre. It is one of the most rooted fears in human experience. Body horror is a sub-genre in horror films that has since been one of popular culture's most obscure segments. These particular artworks are inspired by the works of one of the pioneer of body horror movie making, the Canadian director, David Cronenberg. The manipulation, mutilation, and mutation of the body is almost identical to the ways of humans have evolved, as shown in Cronenberg's films. The mutilated bodies of the characters, predominantly in the protagonists, answers our deep lying questions about what truly scares us , really lived inside of us. Since then, the manipulation of the body has been the tentpole component of what makes science fiction & horror movies. This is an ode to that birth of the sub-genre. #32artaward #makealegacy

A project series of conceptual visualisation of visions of future Indonesia, as presumably envisioned by fictional architects of Indonesia in the 60s & 70s. These buildings in this project represents the spirit of a better Indonesia, automated, utopian, and grounded reality. In a form of conceptual illustrations and architectural renderings of places that probably will take place in the 22nd century Indonesia (or future). The concept propose a story of an underground creative movement that takes place in the New Order in Indonesia (era Orde Baru). Due to differences of ideology and views with the recent government, the new emerging creative forces morphed a collective of design projects that will oversee Indonesia reaching its true potential as a country. Through advanced technology that way ahead of its time, young architects and designers forged a vision that bears hope and vision of a better, evolved, advanced Indonesia. 
Collaboration with @alifhadien 
#32artaward #makealegacy

caption.text: Harkonnen Magazine adalah sebuah karya ilustrasi/desain grafis berseri yang berkonsep majalah fiksional yang mengulas tentang perkembangan dan isu-isu mengenai gaya hidup umat manusia seiring dengan pemanfaatan teknologi, dan integrasi antara teknologi dan kehidupan manusia sehari-hari. Majalah ini mengulas isu-isu yang menantang norma-norma dan nilai kemanusiaan yang sudah menjadi lazim demi kemajuan dan evolusi kemanusiaan. Isu-isu ini bersifat fiksional dan berdasarkan landasan pencapaian teknologi di masa kini, majalah ini bersifat sebagai fiksi spekulatif (speculative fiction) yang memprediksi kehidupan umat manusia di masa depan yang sudah berintegrasi dengan teknologi, masalah-masalah kompleks yang semakin timbul akibat perubahan nilai-nilai kemanusiaan yang harus menghadapi perubahan zaman, dan perubahan manusia sendiri (evoulsi manusia). #32artaward #makealegacy
